doc.previous: The first attempt to launch the Silesian Wikipedia project took place in March 2006,[1] but because of negative comments in the discussion section, the proposal was rejected.[2]
doc.after: In 2007 officially registered the Silesian language in its list of languages.[clarification needed] The International Linguistic Organization SIL International followed this step in 18 July 2007 and International Organization for Standardization (ISO) assigned it the ISO code "szl".[3][4][5][6]
